(1. PURPOSE AND SCOPE) Tj
0 0 Td
50 704 Td
(1.1 This Standard Operating Procedure defines the tactics, techniques and procedures) Tj
0 0 Td
50 692 Td
(for a two-fireteam section conducting a deliberate attack on a fixed enemy position.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 680 Td
(1.2 This SOP applies to all section-level assaults conducted by E-Squadron elements) Tj
0 0 Td
50 668 Td
(in combined arms and independent operations.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 656 Td
(1.3 All ranks are expected to know and execute this SOP without prompting.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 636 Td
(2. DEFINITIONS) Tj
0 0 Td
50 624 Td
(2.1 Section: Two fireteams \(Alpha and Bravo\) totalling 8-10 personnel under a) Tj
0 0 Td
50 612 Td
(Section Commander \(SC\) and 2IC.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 600 Td
(2.2 Support-by-Fire \(SBF\): Designated fire position from which one element provides) Tj
0 0 Td
50 588 Td
(suppressing fire while the other manoeuvres.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 576 Td
(2.3 Breach Point: The designated entry point into the objective area.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 564 Td
(2.4 ERV: Emergency Rendezvous - fallback point if communications are lost.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 552 Td
(2.5 SITREP: Situation Report - standardised report format passed to higher command.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 532 Td
(3. PRE-ASSAULT ADMINISTRATION) Tj
0 0 Td
50 520 Td
(3.1 ORDERS GROUP) Tj
0 0 Td
50 508 Td
(a\) SC delivers full orders using the standard 7-paragraph format \(SMEAC\).) Tj
0 0 Td
50 496 Td
(b\) All element commanders confirm understanding and brief their teams.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 484 Td
(c\) Questions answered before move to line of departure.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 472 Td
(3.2 EQUIPMENT CHECKS) Tj
0 0 Td
50 460 Td
(a\) All personnel conduct personal weapon checks - cleared, loaded, safety on.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 448 Td
(b\) Magazines: minimum 3 full magazines per rifleman, 4 per automatic weapon.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 436 Td
(c\) Grenades: 2 fragmentation, 2 smoke per fireteam minimum.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 424 Td
(d\) Communications: Primary and alternate nets tested and confirmed.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 412 Td
(e\) Medical: Individual first field dressings confirmed on person.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 400 Td
(3.3 REHEARSALS) Tj
0 0 Td
50 388 Td
(a\) Dry run of breach and clearance conducted at model or on ground if time permits.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 376 Td
(b\) Actions on contact rehearsed by all elements.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 364 Td
(c\) Casevac procedure and casualty collection point \(CCP\) confirmed.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 344 Td
(4. ASSAULT SEQUENCE) Tj
0 0 Td
50 332 Td
(4.1 APPROACH) Tj
0 0 Td
50 320 Td
(a\) Section moves tactically to the forming-up place \(FUP\) using bounding overwatch.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 308 Td
(b\) Noise and light discipline enforced throughout approach.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 296 Td
(c\) SC confirms final coords and adjusts plan if situation has changed.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 284 Td
(4.2 DEPLOYMENT FROM FUP) Tj
0 0 Td
50 272 Td
(a\) Alpha Fireteam deploys left flank, moves to flanking assault position.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 260 Td
(b\) Bravo Fireteam moves to Support-by-Fire position on the high ground or) Tj
0 0 Td
50 248 Td
(best available cover with line of sight to the objective.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 236 Td
(c\) Both elements confirm in position via radio before fire is opened.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 224 Td
(4.3 FIRE AND MANOEUVRE) Tj
0 0 Td
50 212 Td
(a\) SC gives execute signal - two radio clicks or designated code word.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 200 Td
(b\) Bravo opens fire immediately, suppressing enemy position.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 188 Td
(c\) Alpha initiates the assault, advancing in short bounds using fire and movement.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 176 Td
(d\) Alpha confirms breach point clear before entry.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 164 Td
(e\) Bravo shifts fire to flanks and depth on Alpha's confirmation of breach.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 152 Td
(4.4 CLEARANCE PROCEDURE) Tj
0 0 Td
50 140 Td
(a\) Alpha clears room by room using standard two-man entry drill.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 128 Td
(b\) Callout system: CLEAR or NOT CLEAR after each room or position.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 116 Td
(c\) No element moves past unsecured rooms or positions.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 104 Td
(d\) Bravo collapses inward once Alpha confirms objective 75 percent clear.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 92 Td
(e\) All personnel maintain trigger discipline - positive ID before engaging.) Tj
0 0 Td
50 72 Td
